This is a beta version. Please, don't hesitate to reach to us on enterprise@domainiq.com for customized solutions/extension of functionality or if you found an error.
  1) Setup. To work with the software you'll need to setup your domainIQ API key. IF you have it, navigate to the Setup page and enter your key there. If the key is correct, you'll see a message that will say that your key is successfully verified and updated.
  If you don't have a key yet, please, register at domainiq.com
  2) Whois. If you want to query a single domain, please use the whois page.
  3) Reverse whois. Use this page for name and e-mail search queries.
  4) Extended reverse search. You can query IP, MX address, DNS and Google Analytics. 
  5) Whois history. You can find a history of registrant names and registrant emails for a given domain
  6) DomainIQ API - if you want to get raw data from domainIQ API, you can plug in the link to the data that you want to get into your pipeline through this page. Recommended for advanced users. It can't format the data in the Splunk table yet, so you'll have to format the json yourself. 
  7) All the commands outlined here are also accessible through general Splunk search. Syntax for Splunk searches is outputted on each interface page after your make a search query.